From 2c4d2a83da7c0b34bb90b16a77a82e2e54a50d4f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Jun 2025 16:03:53 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Introduce helpers for PSD
 limit and non-puncture regulatory mask calculation

Add initial support for calculating minimum Power Spectral Density (PSD)
limits and regulatory masks for non-punctured channels in the 6 GHz band.

Introduce get_psd_limit(), a helper function that iterates through the
Automated Frequency Coordination (AFC) frequency object list to determine
the minimum PSD limit applicable to a given frequency. Ensure the most
restrictive PSD value is selected when multiple overlapping frequency
ranges are present.

Add get_y_val(), a utility function that performs linear interpolation
between two points. Use this to compute intermediate dB reduction values
for shaping regulatory masks with smooth transitions.

Add get_regmask_non_puncture(), which calculates the regulatory mask for
non-punctured channels based on the offset from the center frequency and
the channel bandwidth. Apply predefined attenuation thresholds and
slope-based reductions to determine the mask value.

Define the following constants and macros to support PSD and regulatory
mask logic:
- INVALID_EDGE, INVALID_DBR, INVALID_PSD: sentinel values for error
  handling
- DEFAULT_LOW_6GFREQ and DEFAULT_HIGH_6GFREQ: define the 6 GHz band range
- MAX_PUNC_MASK_LIMITS: maximum number of offset/dB reduction pairs per
  mask
- PUNCTURE_* macros: define valid puncture bitmaps for 40/80/160/320 MHz
  bandwidths

Introduce struct punct_mask, which holds up to three offset and dB
reduction (dbr) pairs used to define the shape of a regulatory mask for a
punctured region.

Add enum puncture_type to classify puncture configurations:
- PUNCTURE_TYPE_EDGE: edge-only puncture
- PUNCTURE_TYPE_INTERIM_20_PLUS: interim puncture wider than 20 MHz
- PUNCTURE_TYPE_INTERIM_20: exactly 20 MHz interim puncture
- PUNCTURE_TYPE_INVALID: fallback for unrecognized patterns

Define static dB reduction profiles for each puncture type:
- pdbm1[] for edge puncture shaping
- pdbm2[] for interim 20+ MHz shaping
- pdbm3[] for interim 20 MHz shaping

Use these helpers and definitions in subsequent patches to implement full
PSD enforcement logic that accounts for puncture masks and ensures
compliance with Out-of-Band Emission (OOBE) constraints.

Fixes: None
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency:
n00-001-hostapd-add-support-for-6GHz-operation.patch
